<paragraph blockId="4.[213,1169,289,728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="799">
<materialsCitation box="[213,1169,289,313]" elevation="28" location="Fan Tsang Chau (Conic Island) Cave" pageId="4" pageNumber="799" specimenCount="1" specimenCount-juvenile="1">
One adult, 
<specimenCount box="[341,477,289,313]" pageId="4" pageNumber="799" type="juvenile">one juvenile</specimenCount>
from 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03D387FED23FFFA8FDE5CBE0BAB1FD4A:8EA56033D23FFFA8FDD1CA69B8FCFEAB" box="[549,981,289,313]" name="Fan Tsang Chau (Conic Island) Cave" pageId="4" pageNumber="799">Fan Tsang Chau (Conic Island) Cave</location>
, station D, 
<quantity box="[1116,1169,289,313]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="799" unit="m" value="28.0">
<elevation box="[1116,1169,289,313]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="799" unit="m" value="28.0">28 m</elevation>
</quantity>
</materialsCitation>
in from the cave mouth, depth 
<quantity box="[575,652,321,345]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.23" pageId="4" pageNumber="799" unit="m" value="12.3">12.3 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[213,1169,289,728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="799">
The adult specimen agrees well with the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kinberg" authorityYear="1856" box="[906,1059,353,377]" class="Polychaeta" family="Iphionidae" genus="Iphione" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="799" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ovata">
<emphasis box="[906,1059,353,377]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="799">Iphione ovata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pettibone MH" box="[213,401,385,409]" pageId="4" pageNumber="799" pagination="1 - 43" refId="ref10218" refString="Pettibone MH. 1986. Review of the Iphioninae (Polychaeta: Polynoidae) and revision of Iphione cimex Quatrefages, Gattyana deludens Fauvel, and Harmothoe iphionelloides Johnson (Harmothoinae). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 428: 1 - 43." type="journal article" year="1986">Pettibone (1986)</bibRefCitation>
; the other specimen is a juvenile which probably also belongs to this species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pettibone MH" box="[308,498,417,441]" pageId="4" pageNumber="799" pagination="1 - 43" refId="ref10218" refString="Pettibone MH. 1986. Review of the Iphioninae (Polychaeta: Polynoidae) and revision of Iphione cimex Quatrefages, Gattyana deludens Fauvel, and Harmothoe iphionelloides Johnson (Harmothoinae). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 428: 1 - 43." type="journal article" year="1986">Pettibone (1986)</bibRefCitation>
records this species as widely distributed in tropical and subtropical regions of the eastern, central and western Pacific and Indian Oceans and the Red Sea, mainly in intertidal and shallow depths, associated with coral reefs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[213,1169,289,728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="799">
One other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[490,572,513,537]" class="Polychaeta" family="Iphionidae" genus="Iphione" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="799" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[490,572,513,537]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="799">Iphione</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Savigny, 1818)" baseAuthorityName="Savigny" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[587,894,513,537]" class="Polychaeta" family="Iphionidae" genus="Iphione" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="799" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="muricata">
<emphasis box="[587,709,513,537]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="799">I. muricata</emphasis>
(Savigny, 1818)
</taxonomicName>
, has been reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[213,350,545,569]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="4" pageNumber="799">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mak PMS" box="[393,526,545,569]" pageId="4" pageNumber="799" pagination="595 - 617" refId="ref9736" refString="Mak PMS. 1982. The coral associated polychaetes of Hong Kong, with special reference to the serpulids. In: Morton B, Tseng CK, editors. The marine flora and fauna of Hong Kong and southern China. Proceedings of the first international marine biological workshop: the marine flora and fauna of Hong Kong and southern China; 18 April - 10 May 1980; Hong Kong. Hong Kong: Hong Kong University Press. p. 595 - 617." type="book chapter" year="1982">Mak (1982)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hanley JR" box="[584,748,545,569]" pageId="4" pageNumber="799" pagination="361 - 369" refId="ref9093" refString="Hanley JR. 1992. Checklist of scaleworms (Polychaeta: Polynoidae) from Hong Kong. In: Morton B, editor. The marine flora and fauna of Hong Kong and southern China III. Proceedings of the fourth international marine biological workshop: the marine flora and fauna of Hong Kong and southern China; 11 - 29 April 1989; Hong Kong. Hong Kong: Hong Kong University Press. p. 361 - 369." type="book chapter" year="1992">Hanley (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Wu B &amp; Wu Q &amp; Qiu J &amp; Lu H" box="[810,994,545,569]" pageId="4" pageNumber="799" refId="ref10986" refString="Wu B, Wu Q, Qiu J, Lu H. 1997. Fauna Sinica. Phylum Annelida Class Polychaeta Order Phyllodocimorpha. Beijing: Science Press." type="book" year="1997">Wu et al. (1997)</bibRefCitation>
list this species from the South 
<collectingCountry box="[402,471,577,601]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="799">China</collectingCountry>
Sea. The scales of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Savigny" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[703,828,577,601]" class="Polychaeta" family="Iphionidae" genus="Iphione" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="799" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="muricata">
<emphasis box="[703,828,577,601]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="799">I. muricata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a lateral fringe of long cylindrical spinous papillae, whereas those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kinberg" authorityYear="1856" box="[744,830,609,633]" class="Polychaeta" family="Iphionidae" genus="Iphione" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="799" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ovata">
<emphasis box="[744,830,609,633]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="799">I. ovata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a smooth edge. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Savigny" baseAuthorityYear="1818" class="Polychaeta" family="Iphionidae" genus="Iphione" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="799" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="muricata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="799">Iphione muricata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is another species widely distributed in tropical and subtropical regions of the Indo-Pacific, in mainly intertidal and shallow water, associated with coral reefs (
<bibRefCitation author="Pettibone MH" box="[220,397,704,728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="799" pagination="1 - 43" refId="ref10218" refString="Pettibone MH. 1986. Review of the Iphioninae (Polychaeta: Polynoidae) and revision of Iphione cimex Quatrefages, Gattyana deludens Fauvel, and Harmothoe iphionelloides Johnson (Harmothoinae). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 428: 1 - 43." type="journal article" year="1986">Pettibone 1986</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
